  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to show the impact of a pain diary on the communication of pain
      by pediatric patients. Participants will be given a pain diary after consent and asked to
      complete the record each time they have pain. A survey about the efficacy of the pain diary
      will be taken prior to discharge by the nurse, physician, patient and parents. The hypothesis
      is that the pain diary will improve the communication.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
